2.text: What is your main exercise type?

3.text: How many hours of exercise do you perform each week?

4.text: How do you feel if you have to miss exercise/training?

5.text: Please enter your current height (in metres e.g. 1.65)

6.text: Please enter your current weight (in kg)

7.text: Please enter your lowest weight for your current height (in kg)

8.text: How often do you weight yourself per week?

9.text: How old were you when you had your first period?

10.text: To assess your current menstrual hormones, please indicate the regularity of your menstrual periods.
10.answer: I no longer have menstrual periods, as I have reached menopause

11.text: Have your periods ever stopped for 3 or more consecutive months (besides pregnancy or taking hormonal contraception or reaching menopause)?

12.text: During the last year how many days off exercise/training have you had due to injury?

13.text: During the last year how many soft tissue injuries, e.g. muscle, ligament, tendon, joint (excluding fractures) have you had?

14.text: Of these soft tissue injuries, how many were recurrent (i.e. in the same place, or same type of injury)?

15.text: If you had bone injuries how many of these were recurrent, i.e. same place, or same type of injury?

16.text: If you have had any type of fractures, where have these been located? Check all that apply.

19.text: Do you exclude carbohydrates from your diet?

21.text: How would you rate your levels of freshness over the past year?

22.text: How would you rate your sleep quality over the past year?

23.text: How would you rate your digestive system over the past year?

24.text: How does controlling what you eat affect the way you feel about yourself?

25.text: How does controlling what you weigh affect the way you feel about yourself?

26.text: Have you ever been diagnosed with an eating disorder?

interpretation: Potential concern, suggesting that you may need to address imbalances between you training load, nutrition and recovery.  You are strongly advised to consider seeking expert help to explore ways to improve your health and performance.
